ca.uqac.lif.cep.fol

Class Interpretation

  • java.lang.Object
    • ca.uqac.lif.cep.fol.Interpretation

  • public class Interpretation
extends Object
    A context in which predicates can be evaluated.

    An Interpretation implements the corresponding concept from first-order logic. It defines sets of values, each associated with a name, called the domains. It also defines a set of predicates, each.

    Author:
    Sylvain Hall√©

    • Field Detail

      • m_domains

        protected Map<String,Set<Object>> m_domains
        The domains defined for this interpretation. The key of this map is the name of each domain, and the corresponding value is the set of values in this domain.

      • m_predicates

        protected Map<String,Predicate> m_predicates
        The predicates defined for this interpretation. The key of this map is the name of each predicate, and the value is the corresponding Predicate object.
